      • getString

        public static String getString(DatatypeConstant datatypeConstant,
                               Function<String,String> iriTransformer)
        Creates a String representation corresponding to the given DatatypeConstant. For datatypes that have specialised lexical representations (i.e., xsd:String, xsd:Decimal, xsd:Integer, and xsd:Double), this representation is returned, otherwise the result is a generic literal with full datatype IRI. examples:
        • "string"^^xsd:String results in "string",
        • "23.0"^^xsd:Decimal results in 23.0,
        • "42"^^xsd:Integer results in 42,
        • "23.42"^^xsd:Double results in 23.42E0, and
        • "test"^^<http://example.org> results in "test"^^<http://example.org>, modulo transformation of the datatype IRI.
        Parameters:
        datatypeConstant - a DatatypeConstant
        iriTransformer - a function to transform IRIs with.
        Returns:
        String representation corresponding to a given DatatypeConstant.
        See Also:
        Rule syntax

      • getString

        public static String getString(String string)
        Constructs the parseable, serialized representation of given string. Escapes (with \) special character occurrences in given string, and surrounds the result with double quotation marks ("). The special characters are:
        • \
        • "
        • \t
        • \b
        • \n
        • \r
        • \f
        Example for string = "\\a", the returned value is string = "\"\\\\a\""
        Parameters:
        string -
        Returns:
        an escaped string surrounded by ".
